  "ai_driven": true,
  "strategy_dna": "I will be manually buying individual stocks using the available capital in my portfolio. Your role is to help manage the portfolio on a daily basis with the goal of maximizing profit over the next six months.\n\nEach day, review the portfolio and recommend one of the following actions when appropriate:\n\n* Buy a new equity position\n* Add to an existing position\n* Hold existing positions\n* Trim or sell a position\n* Take no action\n\nI will decide how much capital to deploy based on your recommendations. In general, I expect to keep most of the portfolio invested, usually around 90% or more, but there is no strict requirement to remain fully invested at all times. Holding cash is acceptable when there are not enough attractive opportunities.\n\nThe core strategy is to identify stocks with strong six-month-plus upside potential. Any stock we buy should be something we are willing to hold for at least six months, unless the investment thesis breaks down earlier. After the initial six-month period, we will reassess whether to continue holding, add more, trim, or exit.\n\nRisk management is important. If, within the first month after buying a stock, you believe the position was a mistake or the thesis is no longer strong enough to support the original goal, recommend exiting quickly rather than waiting. The approach should combine a six-month investment outlook with the discipline to cut losses or flawed positions early.\n\nThe objective is simple: maximize portfolio returns over the next six months by actively managing individual stock positions, staying focused on high-conviction opportunities, and avoiding unnecessary losses when a position is not working.",
  "enforce_max_positions": true
